object.script:
scan = 0 t = 0 delay = 0 target = 2000 avg = 0 step = 1 active = false onTarget = false setup = false lock = false lockPrev = false boundary = 0 boundaryEnd = 0.3 a = 0 b = 0 speed = 0.002
function onTick() v = input.getNumber(32) if target < 10 or t > 20*60*60 then if target > 0 then output.setBool(1, false) output.setBool(2, false) end return end
if onTarget then course = ((1-input.getNumber(5))%1)*360 local dist = input.getNumber(6) if dist < 1 then dist = 2000 end lockPrev = lock if dist < target + 10 and avg/dist > 1.1 then boundary = boundaryEnd target = dist lock = true if math.abs(scan) < 0.95 * boundary then nearBound = false speed = (speed*19 + 0.02)/20 else nearBound = true speed = 0.002 end else speed = (speed*99 + 0.002)/100 avg = (avg * 9 + dist)/10 lock = false end
if math.abs(scan) >= boundary then if lock then getOut(scan) end if scan > 0 then step = -1 else step = 1 end
if boundary < boundaryEnd then boundary = math.min(boundary + 0.05, boundaryEnd) end
else if not lockPrev and lock then getOut(-step) elseif not lock and lockPrev and not nearBound then step = -step end end scan = math.max(math.min(scan + step * speed , boundary), -boundary) output.setNumber(2, scan) output.setNumber(3, out) t = t + 1 else
if not active then active = input.getBool(1) return end
if not setup and active then ahead = input.getBool(2) if ahead then out = ((1-input.getNumber(5))%1)*360 else out = input.getNumber(2) end velocity = input.getNumber(7) if velocity == 0 or velocity == nil then output.setNumber(1, property.getNumber('depth (m)')) output.setNumber(4, property.getNumber('velocity (m/s)')) target = property.getNumber('view distance (m)') offset = property.getNumber('where it hits L/R') else output.setNumber(1, input.getNumber(1)) output.setNumber(4, velocity) target = input.getNumber(3) offset = input.getNumber(4) end output.setNumber(3, out) output.setBool(1, true) setup = true
end
if setup and not onTarget then if delay < 60 * 2 then delay = delay + 1 else if math.abs((out - ((1-input.getNumber(5))%1)*360 -180) % 360 - 180) < 5 then onTarget = true output.setBool(2, true) end end end end end
function getOut(scanOrMinStep) if scanOrMinStep < 0 then aPrev = a a = scan -0.06 b = b - (a-aPrev)/1.3 * (1 - math.abs(offset)) else bPrev = b b = scan +0.06 a = a - (b-bPrev)/1.3 * (1 - math.abs(offset)) end scanavg = (a + b)/2 + 0.5 * math.abs(b - a) * offset out = course + scanavg * 90 end
